No matter your stance on nuclear energy, this is huge. Energy Secretary Jennifer Granholm announced yesterday that for the first time ever, fusion ignition has been achieved at the Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, National Ignition Facility. She states this process will allow “creating more energy from fusion reactions than the energy used to start the process.” She later stated that “Ignition allows us to replicate for the first time certain conditions that are found only in the stars and the sun.” Let’s talk about it.

“America loves MLK as an *idea* - I’ve already seen the enemies of MLK’s message quoting him as one of their “heroes” as MLK Day approaches 🙄🙄” 

########

A lot of ⚪️ people where posting MLK quotes yesterday which is ironic given most of them give 0 fucks about equality & equity for black & brown folks. So naturally I had to break away from the pack to say:
If you are white, you are also racist (including myself) 🛑 & #read 

It’s OK to admit this. Through indoctrination via education, news, media, photography, art, finance, social groups… LIFE. America teaches us to be racist shortly after birth. It’s not your fault what you were fed as a baby. But it IS your responsibility as an adult to dismantle WS within yourself right now. Speak OUT when you see it happening. I didn’t know MLK, but I think having *more* white people work on BEING anti-racist would align more appropriately with Dr. King’s vision than some superficial obligatory fake #instagram post of the day where most will not follow any other ACTION beyond that. #trifling ## #psa DONT QUOTE MLK IF YOU ARE: 
*PRO* Police
*ANTI* BLM,
PRO capitalism, 
a JAN 6th insurrectionist

Part of being anti-racist is learning the history that wasn’t taught in school.

Mentally ill. Deviant. Diseased. And in need of a cure.

These were among the terms psychiatrists used to describe lesbians and gay men in the 1950s, 1960s, and early 1970s. According to the medical establishment, every gay person — no matter how well-adjusted — suffered from a mental disorder. And as long as lesbians and gay men were “sick,” progress toward equality was impossible.
“CURED” chronicles the battle waged by a small group of @activists who declared war against a formidable institution — and won a crucial victory in the modern movement for LGBTQ equality. This feature-length documentary takes viewers inside the David-versus-Goliath struggle that led the American Psychiatric Association to remove homosexuality from its manual of mental illnesses in 1973. 
Viewers meet the key players who achieved this victory, along with allies and opponents within the APA. The film illuminates the strategy and tactics that led to this pivotal yet largely unknown moment. Indeed, following the Stonewall uprising of 1969, the campaign that culminated in the APA’s decision marks the first major step on the path to first-class citizenship for LGBTQ Americans.

On June 14, join the Downtown Alliance at Alamo Drafthouse Lower Manhattan (@alamonyc )for a screening of “CURED,” followed by a conversation between activists Reverend Magora Kennedy, Jack Drescher, MD and journalist and historian Charles Kaiser. The discussion will dig into the lived experiences of our speakers during the 1970s and their work, which transformed not just LGBTQ people’s perceptions of themselves, but also the social fabric of America.

Tickets are $5 and include popcorn and a beverage. All proceeds will be donated to Safe Place International.
@downtownnyc @patricksammondc #lgbtq🌈 #pride #gaypride #film #documentary #mustsee #share #june14th #nyc #newyork

We see it every year, corporations attempting to “back” LGBTQ people with #pride advertisements to solely get our dollar. We often see that on July 1st, they go right back to “normal programming”. In many cases, these companies split their political support and donations to the Republican Party to support anti-gay legislation. What’s happening this year is that companies like @target are afraid to do the Pride advertising because of the violence it’s causing their employees. It’s important for the #lgbtq community to harvest our spending power especially during #pridemonth . We can’t control what Target does, but we don’t need to buy their products. We need to send strong bottom line messaging to CEO’s like @bria_ncornell 
#repost @themilajam @ukecurious #boycotttarget #gaypride #pride🌈 #lgbtq🌈 #lgbtqia #june2023

Happy #juneteenth !!! For those that don’t know or don’t understand, this is now a FEDERAL holiday. If you aren’t clear on why or unaware of the history, take this time to learn. 

I was having a conversation with a white guy who said things like “what kinda holiday is it?” I explained. “No I mean I know what it is, but what the fuck kinda holiday is it? It’s a nothing holiday like Memorial Day or Presidents’ Day”. I had to take this time to correct him and also ask him to look at why he thinks that. Would he say that about July 4th or Christmas? We all know white peoples are saying these things or why companies are considering this a “floating” holiday (aka optional). Black people have been the target of oppression from day 1 in America and after all this time and BLM, we still can’t all be on the same page about the significance of this Holiday?? SWIPE —> RIGHT to learn :)

#celebratejuneteenth #itsarealholiday #read #learn #getyourselfuptospeed #repost 🙏🙏 @missnicolagorham

Hello friends and family
I'm so sorry to have to share that I have been diagnosed with a very aggressive form of Stage 4 Non-Hodgkins Lymphoma. My doctors reassure me this is curable, but it's going to take a lot of fighting for the next 6. I'm not gonna lie, it's been a struggle since my diagnosis. I have pain everyday, I can only stay on my feet for so long. I have lymph nodes all thru body that are enlarged and inflamed.
Those of you who know me, know that I have always been a very hard worker. I have always had a job and always only depended on myself. I am a professional actor, acting coach and I run own private party staffing company providing bartenders and servers for private parties and events. Since being diagnosed I am not able to work like I normally would. Taking care of my health has now become a full time job. I am not making and cannot make the income I was before this happened. After my recovery, I plan on getting back on my hustle. But in the meantime, I’m asking for everyone’s help to get me thru this next 6-8 months. (Cont. in comments)
